  "text": "Because rDNA is present in higher copy numbers ($10,000 copies) in the MAC [CITATION_1] , compared with all other MAC chromosomes ($50-70 copies), we suspected that the observed effect might be limited to the rDNA locus. However, we detected similar inhibition of DNA elimination by introducing the CL1 or M IES into the BTU1 locus, which is located on a typical MAC chromosome ( Figures S3A and S3B ). This result is consistent with the fact that once IES retention is induced by the introduction of an IES into rDNA, the retained IES at the endogenous (non-high-copy) locus is sufficient to inhibit its elimination in the subsequent sexual generations [CITATION_2] (see also Figure S2 ).",
