      "span_text": "This result is consistent with the fact that once IES retention is induced by the introduction of an IES into rDNA, the retained IES at the endogenous (non-high-copy) locus is sufficient to inhibit its elimination in the subsequent sexual generations [CITATION_2] (see also Figure S2 )."
